Eva Gaëlle Green -LRB- -LSB- ɡʁin -RSB- ; -LSB- ˈɡɾeːn -RSB- ; born 6 July 1980 -RRB- is a French actress and model .
She started her career in theatre before making her film debut in 2003 in Bernardo Bertolucci 's film The Dreamers .
She achieved international recognition when she appeared as Sibylla , Queen of Jerusalem in Ridley Scott 's historical epic Kingdom of Heaven -LRB- 2005 -RRB- , and portrayed Bond girl Vesper Lynd in the James Bond film Casino Royale -LRB- 2006 -RRB- .
In 2006 , Green was awarded the BAFTA Rising Star Award .
Since 2006 , Green has starred in independent films Cracks -LRB- 2009 -RRB- , Womb -LRB- 2010 -RRB- , and Perfect Sense -LRB- 2011 -RRB- .
She has also appeared in the television series Camelot -LRB- 2011 -RRB- , and played Angelique Bouchard in Tim Burton 's big-screen adaptation of Dark Shadows -LRB- 2012 -RRB- .
In 2014 , she played Artemisia in the 300 sequel , 300 : Rise of an Empire -LRB- 2014 -RRB- , and Ava Lord in Frank Miller 's and Robert Rodriguez 's Sin City sequel , Sin City : A Dame to Kill For -LRB- 2014 -RRB- .
She also starred as Vanessa Ives in Showtime 's horror drama Penny Dreadful -LRB- 2014 -- 16 -RRB- .
Her performance in the series earned her a nomination for Best Actress in a Television Series -- Drama at the 73rd Golden Globe Awards .
In 2016 , she played the titular character in Tim Burton 's fantasy film Miss Peregrine 's Home for Peculiar Children .